[SN]TITLE[SN]
Southampton man dies following M27 crash

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has died a week after the car he was travelling in crashed and overturned on the M27 in Hampshire.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 20-year-old, from Bitterne, Southampton, was a rear-seat passenger when the Vauxhall Corsa crashed on the eastbound carriageway, between Fareham and Portsmouth, on 26 June.
The driver, 20, suffered serious injuries but has since been discharged from hospital.
A front-seat passenger, 19, who sustained a head injury, is "stable".
Police are appealing for witnesses to the accident.
